President Trump delivered remarks at an event celebrating African American History Month in the East Room of the White House. He praised the contributions of African Americans to American culture, faith, community, and values. He also highlighted the achievements of African American individuals in various fields, such as sports, music, and science. The President discussed his administration's efforts to create jobs, improve education, and reform the criminal justice system for the benefit of African Americans. He thanked the attendees and reiterated his commitment to working towards equal opportunity for all Americans.